HEADWORD: Pertusion
<hw>Per*tu"sion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[L.
<ets>pertusio</ets>.]</ety> <def>The act of punching or piercing with a
pointed instrument; <as>as, <ex>pertusion</ex> of a vein</as>.</def>
<mark>[R.]</mark> <rj><au>Arbuthnot.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>A punched hole; a perforation.</def>
<rj><au>Bacon.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pertussis</ent>⟦br⟧
